Headlines.Headline: Danone Cuts Chinese Baby Milk Products Prices by Up to 20%

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Ruth Bender PARIS--Danone SA (BN.FR) Monday said it will cut prices for its baby formula products in China by up to 20% after Chinese authorities launched an investigation into possible price fixing by foreign companies on the highly lucrative Chinese baby-food market. Danone, which last week already said it would cut prices but declined to give details, said it will cut prices for its main Dumex products between 5% and 20%, starting Tuesday. Rival Nestle SA (NESN.VX) said last week also it would cut prices in its Wyeth Nutrition line of baby products by an average of 11% and freeze prices on all new products for the next year as of Monday.
